<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Delta Flyer</td></tr>
<tr id="L1"><td><a href="#L1">1</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok is in the pilot's seat, Neelix is behind him, tapping his fingers.</td></tr>

<tr id="L2"><td><a href="#L2">2</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Mister Neelix.</td></tr>

<tr id="L3"><td><a href="#L3">3</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Sorry. How about a game of Species, Starship or Anomaly?</td></tr>

<tr id="L4"><td><a href="#L4">4</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Surely you could find something more productive to occupy your time.</td></tr>

<tr id="L5"><td><a href="#L5">5</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Come on, Tuvok, it'll be fun. You think of something, species, anomaly, or starship, and I have fifteen questions to guess what it is. Come on, come on, come on, come on.</td></tr>

<tr id="L6"><td><a href="#L6">6</a></td><td>TUVOK:  I would prefer some peace and quiet.</td></tr>

<tr id="L7"><td><a href="#L7">7</a></td><td>NEELIX:  How about a riddle?</td></tr>

<tr id="L8"><td><a href="#L8">8</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Mister Neelix.</td></tr>

<tr id="L9"><td><a href="#L9">9</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Come on, it'll be fun.</td></tr>

<tr id="L10"><td><a href="#L10">10</a></td><td>TUVOK:  I have no desire for fun.</td></tr>

<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Okay, forget fun. A good riddle can stimulate the mind. Now, no self-respecting Vulcan could say no to that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Very well. One riddle.</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Okay, here goes. A lone Ensign finds himself stranded on a class L planetoid with no rations. His only possession, a calendar. When Starfleet finds him twelve months later, he's in perfect health. Why didn't he starve to death?</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>TUVOK:  It is a theoretical possibility that such planetoids contain hot water springs, which could sustain the man for several weeks.</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>NEELIX:  But not for a whole year.</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>TUVOK:  I concur. Logic dictates that the Ensign in question would perish.</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Ah ha, ha ha! I stumped you. As a matter of fact, he not only survived, but his belly was full. Why? Because he feasted on dates from the calendar.</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Your answer is merely wordplay, it has no basis in reality. Now, if you'll excuse me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L19"><td><a href="#L19">19</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Where are you going?</td></tr>

<tr id="L20"><td><a href="#L20">20</a></td><td>TUVOK:  To find some peace and quiet.</td></tr>

<tr id="L21"><td><a href="#L21">21</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Have fun.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Delta Flyer - aft section</td></tr>
<tr id="L22"><td><a href="#L22">22</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok picks up a PADD to read, then notices one of the screen is active.</td></tr>

<tr id="L23"><td><a href="#L23">23</a></td><td>TUVOK:  Tuvok to Neelix.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Delta Flyer - cockpit</td></tr>
<tr id="L24"><td><a href="#L24">24</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Miss me already, Commander?</td></tr>

