<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Delta Flyer - cockpit</td></tr>
<tr id="L36"><td><a href="#L36">36</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Commander?</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Delta Flyer - aft section</td></tr>
<tr id="L37"><td><a href="#L37">37</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok is lying on the deck, twitching. His tricorder is a smoking wreck.</td></tr>

<tr id="L38"><td><a href="#L38">38</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Tuvok! Delta Flyer to Voyager. Mayday! Tuvok, what happened?</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L39"><td><a href="#L39">39</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok is still twitching, and several large veins are standing out across his face.</td></tr>

<tr id="L40"><td><a href="#L40">40</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Report.</td></tr>

<tr id="L41"><td><a href="#L41">41</a></td><td>EMH:  He's in neuraleptic shock. I'll need another twenty milligrams of synaptizine.</td></tr>

<tr id="L42"><td><a href="#L42">42</a></td><td>NEELIX:  I'll get it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L43"><td><a href="#L43">43</a></td><td>EMH:  It's not working. I'll need to try direct cortical stimulation. Initiate a neurostatic pulse on my mark.</td></tr>

<tr id="L44"><td><a href="#L44">44</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Right.</td></tr>

<tr id="L45"><td><a href="#L45">45</a></td><td>EMH:  Now. Again.</td></tr>

<tr id="L46"><td><a href="#L46">46</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok stops twitching.</td></tr>

<tr id="L47"><td><a href="#L47">47</a></td><td>EMH:  His vital signs have stabilised, for the moment anyway, But he suffered severe neurological trauma.</td></tr>

<tr id="L48"><td><a href="#L48">48</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Do you know what caused it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L49"><td><a href="#L49">49</a></td><td>EMH:  Some kind of alien weapon.</td></tr>

<tr id="L50"><td><a href="#L50">50</a></td><td>NEELIX:  By the time I reached Tuvok, whoever had attacked him was gone.</td></tr>

<tr id="L51"><td><a href="#L51">51</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  What about the surrounding space? Any indication of cloaked vessels?</td></tr>

<tr id="L52"><td><a href="#L52">52</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Between trying to tend to the Commander and piloting the Flyer, I had my hands full. I, I didn't think to scan for cloaked ships. I'm sorry.</td></tr>

<tr id="L53"><td><a href="#L53">53</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  You saved Tuvok's life, Neelix. You have nothing to be sorry about. How do you plan to treat him?</td></tr>

<tr id="L54"><td><a href="#L54">54</a></td><td>EMH:  I won't know until I've run a series of neurological scans, but it would certainly help to know something about the weapon.</td></tr>

<tr id="L55"><td><a href="#L55">55</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Neelix, these Kesat you were negotiating with. Any reason to believe they might know something about this?</td></tr>

<tr id="L56"><td><a href="#L56">56</a></td><td>NEELIX:  It couldn't hurt to ask.</td></tr>

<tr id="L57"><td><a href="#L57">57</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Time to reopen diplomatic channels.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Briefing room</td></tr>
<tr id="L58"><td><a href="#L58">58</a></td><td>NAROQ:  Deputy investigator Naroq, Kesat security. Captain Janeway, Commander Chakotay, Ambassador Neelix.</td></tr>

<tr id="L59"><td><a href="#L59">59</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  You've done your homework.</td></tr>

<tr id="L60"><td><a href="#L60">60</a></td><td>NAROQ:  I familiarised myself with the facts on the way here.</td></tr>

<tr id="L61"><td><a href="#L61">61</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  We're hoping you can help us shed some light on what happened to our crewman.</td></tr>

<tr id="L62"><td><a href="#L62">62</a></td><td>NAROQ:  I believe I can. Based on the information you provided, it is my opinion that he was a victim of the Ba'Neth.</td></tr>

<tr id="L63"><td><a href="#L63">63</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  I've never heard of them.</td></tr>

<tr id="L64"><td><a href="#L64">64</a></td><td>NAROQ:  I'm not surprised. In my language, their name means shadow people. They're a species obsessed with concealing their identity. Extremely paranoid and xenophobic.</td></tr>

<tr id="L65"><td><a href="#L65">65</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Well, that explains their cloaking technology.</td></tr>

<tr id="L66"><td><a href="#L66">66</a></td><td>NAROQ:  It's my belief they've been responsible for several unexplained attacks similar to this one.</td></tr>

<tr id="L67"><td><a href="#L67">67</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Why wasn't I warned about them during my negotiations with your government?</td></tr>

<tr id="L68"><td><a href="#L68">68</a></td><td>NAROQ:  Because my government's official position is that the Ba'Neth do not exist. Most people think they're a myth.</td></tr>

<tr id="L69"><td><a href="#L69">69</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  There's nothing mythical about what happened to Mister Tuvok. Why is your government so sceptical?</td></tr>

<tr id="L70"><td><a href="#L70">70</a></td><td>NAROQ:  Because there've been so few encounters with the Ba'Neth and, well, no one's ever actually seen one.</td></tr>

<tr id="L71"><td><a href="#L71">71</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  How many encounters are we talking about, exactly?</td></tr>

<tr id="L72"><td><a href="#L72">72</a></td><td>NAROQ:  Before this incident? Twelve.</td></tr>

<tr id="L73"><td><a href="#L73">73</a></td><td>CHAKOTAY:  I guess we're lucky thirteen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L74"><td><a href="#L74">74</a></td><td>NAROQ:  You're lucky I gave my supervisor two bottles of Kesatian ale to get this assignment. Any other inspector would have simply attributed Commander Tuvok's injuries to unexplained phenomenon.</td></tr>

<tr id="L75"><td><a href="#L75">75</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  No offence, Mister Naroq, but what makes you so sure the Ba'Neth aren't just a myth?</td></tr>

<tr id="L76"><td><a href="#L76">76</a></td><td>NAROQ:  This incident fits the pattern, Captain. All of the alleged encounters have occurred aboard vessels foreign to this sector. I believe they've been attempts by the Ba'Neth to assess the technology of new arrivals.</td></tr>

<tr id="L77"><td><a href="#L77">77</a></td><td>NEELIX:  They were trying to download tactical data.</td></tr>

<tr id="L78"><td><a href="#L78">78</a></td><td>NAROQ:  And Commander Tuvok suffered severe neural damage. That's also consistent with previous attacks. The Ba'Neth were making sure he would not tell anyone what he saw.</td></tr>

<tr id="L79"><td><a href="#L79">79</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Maybe that's why Tuvok's tricorder was destroyed. They didn't want us to see the cloaking frequency he'd found.</td></tr>

<tr id="L80"><td><a href="#L80">80</a></td><td>NAROQ:  He found a cloaking frequency?</td></tr>

<tr id="L81"><td><a href="#L81">81</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Apparently.</td></tr>

<tr id="L82"><td><a href="#L82">82</a></td><td>NAROQ:  Captain, I don't blame you for finding my theories a bit eccentric. I'm used to it. It's why I'm still a deputy investigator, but I've brought equipment to help your investigation. Let me examine Commander Tuvok and run scans on the vessel where he was attacked. I may finally be able to prove my theories.</td></tr>

<tr id="L83"><td><a href="#L83">83</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  With all due respect, we're more interested in saving Tuvok's life.</td></tr>

<tr id="L84"><td><a href="#L84">84</a></td><td>NAROQ:  If we work together, maybe we can do both.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L85"><td><a href="#L85">85</a></td><td>EMH:  His cognitive, memory and logic centres have all been severely damaged.</td></tr>

<tr id="L86"><td><a href="#L86">86</a></td><td>NAROQ:  But he still has brain activity, which is more than I can say for any of the previous victims.</td></tr>

<tr id="L87"><td><a href="#L87">87</a></td><td>EMH:  Vulcan neural tissue is extremely resilient. I have no doubt that a brain from a lesser species would not have survived.</td></tr>

<tr id="L88"><td><a href="#L88">88</a></td><td>NAROQ:  If you could only tell us what you saw, Mister Tuvok.</td></tr>

<tr id="L89"><td><a href="#L89">89</a></td><td>EMH:  I don't think we'll be hearing from him any time soon.</td></tr>

<tr id="L90"><td><a href="#L90">90</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Keep working. I'll let you know if we find anything that might help. I'll take you to see where the attack occurred.</td></tr>

<tr id="L91"><td><a href="#L91">91</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Janeway and Naroq leave.</td></tr>

<tr id="L92"><td><a href="#L92">92</a></td><td>EMH:  Something I can do for you, Mister Neelix?</td></tr>

<tr id="L93"><td><a href="#L93">93</a></td><td>NEELIX:  I want to help.</td></tr>

<tr id="L94"><td><a href="#L94">94</a></td><td>EMH:  Unless you have a degree in Vulcan neurobiology that I'm not aware of, there's nothing you can do.</td></tr>

<tr id="L95"><td><a href="#L95">95</a></td><td>NEELIX:  There must be something.</td></tr>

<tr id="L96"><td><a href="#L96">96</a></td><td>EMH:  My advice is to return to your quarters and get some rest.</td></tr>

<tr id="L97"><td><a href="#L97">97</a></td><td>NEELIX:  There's no way that I'm going to be able to sleep knowing that Tuvok is lying here like this.</td></tr>

<tr id="L98"><td><a href="#L98">98</a></td><td>EMH:  There have been rare cases in which comatose patients responded to external stimuli. Aromas, touch, voices.</td></tr>

<tr id="L99"><td><a href="#L99">99</a></td><td>NEELIX:  So, you're saying that if I stay here and, and try to talk to Tuvok, I might be able to provoke some sort of response?</td></tr>

<tr id="L100"><td><a href="#L100">100</a></td><td>EMH:  If anyone can provoke Tuvok, Mister Neelix, it's you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L101"><td><a href="#L101">101</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Later, Neelix is wheeling a trolley full of Tuvok's possessions into Sickbay.</td></tr>

<tr id="L102"><td><a href="#L102">102</a></td><td>NEELIX:  Good morning, Tuvok. I brought you a few more items from your quarters to help liven up Sickbay. Your kal-toh game, in case you decide you're ready for a match. Oh, and I also thought that you might enjoy a recitation of that classic proto-Vulcan drama, Clash on the Fire Plains. I'll be performing all twenty three parts myself. I also brought you some flowers from the Airponics bay. Oh, that's fragrant, isn't it? Perhaps you'd enjoy some Vulcan incense. How about some music? Computer, access Vulcan audio file, selection fifty six alpha.</td></tr>

<tr id="L103"><td><a href="#L103">103</a></td><td>EMH:  Mister Neelix. What is that dreadful noise?</td></tr>

<tr id="L104"><td><a href="#L104">104</a></td><td>NEELIX:  The Chants of the Monks of T'Panit. Personally, I think it's dreadful, too, but it's one of Tuvok's favourites.</td></tr>

