<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Delta Flyer - aft section</td></tr>
<tr id="L117"><td><a href="#L117">117</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Commander Chakotay says you've found something.</td></tr>

<tr id="L118"><td><a href="#L118">118</a></td><td>NAROQ:  That, Captain, is an understatement. Listen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L119"><td><a href="#L119">119</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Naroq's device beeps faster as he approaches the bulkhead that wibbled.</td></tr>

<tr id="L120"><td><a href="#L120">120</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  What is it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L121"><td><a href="#L121">121</a></td><td>NAROQ:  The sound of history being made.</td></tr>

<tr id="L122"><td><a href="#L122">122</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Less poetry, Mister Naroq, more facts.</td></tr>

<tr id="L123"><td><a href="#L123">123</a></td><td>NAROQ:  The sound you're hearing indicates the presence of veridium isotopes.</td></tr>

<tr id="L124"><td><a href="#L124">124</a></td><td>SEVEN:  Residual particles from the Ba'Neth's cloaking field.</td></tr>

<tr id="L125"><td><a href="#L125">125</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  You've detected these isotopes before?</td></tr>

<tr id="L126"><td><a href="#L126">126</a></td><td>NAROQ:  Yes, but only after they've decayed. You see, veridium has a very brief half-life, less than seventy hours. The previous sites I've studied have been months, sometimes years old.</td></tr>

<tr id="L127"><td><a href="#L127">127</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  But these isotopes are still active.</td></tr>

<tr id="L128"><td><a href="#L128">128</a></td><td>SEVEN:  We can use Mister Naroq's photolytic converter to illuminate them.</td></tr>

<tr id="L129"><td><a href="#L129">129</a></td><td>NAROQ:  So you see, Captain, why this is an historic moment? We may finally learn what the Ba'Neth look like.</td></tr>

<tr id="L130"><td><a href="#L130">130</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Well, let's see what we've got.</td></tr>

<tr id="L131"><td><a href="#L131">131</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The converter flashes, and a shape starts to form.</td></tr>

<tr id="L132"><td><a href="#L132">132</a></td><td>NAROQ:  You don't know how long I've waited to meet you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L133"><td><a href="#L133">133</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  So the Ba'Neth aren't a myth after all.</td></tr>

<tr id="L134"><td><a href="#L134">134</a></td><td>NAROQ:  This is the clearest image ever captured.</td></tr>

<tr id="L135"><td><a href="#L135">135</a></td><td>SEVEN:  Perhaps. I believe I can adjust our internal sensors to improve it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L136"><td><a href="#L136">136</a></td><td>NAROQ:  What are you doing? You might disrupt the image entirely. Tentacles. I always suspected they were multipeds!</td></tr>

<tr id="L137"><td><a href="#L137">137</a></td><td>EMH [OC]:  Doctor to the Captain. Please report to Sickbay.</td></tr>

<tr id="L138"><td><a href="#L138">138</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  I'm on my way. Seven, if we can integrate Mister Naroq's photolytic technology into the deflector array, we might be able to decloak a Ba'Neth ship.</td></tr>

<tr id="L139"><td><a href="#L139">139</a></td><td>NAROQ:  The technology only works at close range. We have to find the ship before we can expose it. We still need that cloaking frequency.</td></tr>

<tr id="L140"><td><a href="#L140">140</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  One step at a time.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Doctor's office</td></tr>
<tr id="L141"><td><a href="#L141">141</a></td><td>EMH:  The Vulcan brain. A puzzle wrapped inside an enigma housed inside a cranium. Tuvok's neural pathways have begun to bypass the damaged tissue. They're forming new synaptic connections. In effect, his brain is rewiring itself. Whether this is due to my neurostatic therapy, or Neelix's rehabilitation regimen, or some combination of the two I can't be certain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L142"><td><a href="#L142">142</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  Is there any chance he'll make a full recovery?</td></tr>

<tr id="L143"><td><a href="#L143">143</a></td><td>EMH:  It's much too soon to say, but he's alert and he's already regained his basic motor skills.</td></tr>

<tr id="L144"><td><a href="#L144">144</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  But still no speech.</td></tr>

<tr id="L145"><td><a href="#L145">145</a></td><td>NEELIX:  It's only a matter of time, Captain. Look how far he's come already.</td></tr>

<tr id="L146"><td><a href="#L146">146</a></td><td>JANEWAY:  I hope you're right, Neelix, but if he could talk he might be able to tell us something about that cloaking frequency.</td></tr>

<tr id="L147"><td><a href="#L147">147</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Tuvok is enjoying smelling the flowers Neelix brought in.</td></tr>

<tr id="L148"><td><a href="#L148">148</a></td><td>EMH:  We're not sure how much he recalls. For that matter, we're not certain he recognises any of us, or even knows who he is.</td></tr>

<tr id="L149"><td><a href="#L149">149</a></td><td>NEELIX:  I'm going to take him on a tour of the ship. The Doctor thinks that familiar sights and sounds might get the old synaptic juices flowing. Don't worry, Captain. Tuvok will be back to his old self before you can say live long and prosper.</td></tr>

